    "description": "Play this strange little idea that combines turn-based planning with old-school 2D side-scrolling.  I would call this game an experimental strategy game.  Build a deck and get a hand of cards.  Arrange those cards in the order that you want your little robot to follow.  Press play and watch your little obedient robot advance through the stage.<br><br><strong>You take control of a little obedient robot that you kind of program with cards you find.</strong><br><br>Learn your robot's movement cards by practicing with them.  Give them a try and see what each card does.  Once you know how to use them you can plan and try to dodge enemies as you make your way to the exit.<h2 class=\"bb_tag\" ><strong>HOW TO PLAY:</strong></h2><br><strong>You click and drag cards into whatever order you want. </strong><br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1522540/extras/a6719d01fffa90b374a514f936f9bd5b.poster.avif?t=1647274951\" width=600 height=128 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1522540/extras/a6719d01fffa90b374a514f936f9bd5b.webm?t=1647274951\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1522540/extras/a6719d01fffa90b374a514f936f9bd5b.mp4?t=1647274951\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span><br><br><strong>Then when you're ready, hit the play button and watch your robot follow the commands on the cards.</strong><br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1522540/extras/c1573d175c2b56f654e65ab826a84b53.poster.avif?t=1647274951\" width=600 height=210 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1522540/extras/c1573d175c2b56f654e65ab826a84b53.webm?t=1647274951\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1522540/extras/c1573d175c2b56f654e65ab826a84b53.mp4?t=1647274951\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span><br><br><strong>You can add cards to modify your robot's moves.</strong><br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1522540/extras/130636f1d756deb607b80597e456951d.poster.avif?t=1647274951\" width=600 height=338 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1522540/extras/130636f1d756deb607b80597e456951d.webm?t=1647274951\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1522540/extras/130636f1d756deb607b80597e456951d.mp4?t=1647274951\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span><br><br>There are numerous different stages to explore along with dozens of special moves to discover.  The game features at least 2+ hours of gameplay.<br><br><strong><i>*Please note that the game may have some bugs as it is a prototype.  We'll try to squash anything nasty we come across.</i></strong>",
